1
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:14,920
Shicheng.

2
00:00:17,632 --> 00:00:18,760
What are you doing here?

3
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:21,040
You framed me!

4
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:22,200
Why would I frame you?

5
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:24,280
You lost to me
in the student council election

6
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:25,160
last year.

7
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:26,160
You hold a grudge.

8
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:28,400
He's the killer.

9
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:28,960
Case closed.

10
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:34,000
=Cases Between Us=

11
00:00:34,020 --> 00:00:36,112
Someone from the temple said
you showed up yesterday,

12
00:00:36,128 --> 00:00:37,360
wearing cheap pomade.

13
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:38,940
=Episode 7=

14
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:44,800
And an ill-fitting suit
that looked cheap, too.

15
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:47,000
And yours isn't cheap?

16
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:50,720
Paul Poiret.

17
00:00:51,880 --> 00:00:53,760
Bet you've never heard of it.

18
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:54,920
So what if you're rich?

19
00:00:55,960 --> 00:00:57,400
You didn't earn that money yourself.

20
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:03,760
I'd love to earn my own money.

21
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:05,560
But my family stops me.

22
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:10,272
As the pampered young master,

23
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:11,664
I was born with one goal in life.

24
00:01:11,670 --> 00:01:13,800
That's to figure out how
to spend all my family's money.

25
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:15,480
But somehow I just can't. I'm miserable!

26
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:18,320
Shameless jerks

27
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:19,880
are invincible.

28
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:22,920
Pomade,

29
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:23,280
a suit,

30
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,000
and cologne.

31
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,048
You nearly made that Taoist
give up the priesthood.

32
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:31,280
I'm guessing

33
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:36,240
you were meeting a lady.

34
00:01:36,240 --> 00:01:37,520
Don't slander me!

35
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:38,992
You're spitting all over my face!

36
00:01:42,048 --> 00:01:43,080
We found an advanced copy

37
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:45,560
in your dorm yesterday.

38
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,600
It smelled like perfume.

39
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,160
Chanel No. 5.

40
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,360
No way you could afford that.

41
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:55,960
It must've belonged to
some rich young lady.

42
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,600
Stop making things up.

43
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:01,960
I didn't meet anyone.

44
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:03,600
I just want to pray.

45
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,136
Go to a Taoist temple
to pray to Buddha?

46
00:02:05,152 --> 00:02:06,240
That's pretty disrespectful!

47
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:07,520
If you have evidence, say it.

48
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:08,640
If not, let me go.

49
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:11,040
Enough with the lip.

50
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:11,720
Fine.

51
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:14,440
Let's cut to the chase.

52
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:15,360
Last night,

53
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:16,960
you were with that young lady

54
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,176
right up until the murders.

55
00:02:18,192 --> 00:02:20,360
She took you to the Jiuyue Press
to work on an article.

56
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:21,880
That's how you got the advance copy.

57
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:22,480
No.

58
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,280
Lost your nerve?

59
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,000
No.

60
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:29,160
Chief Yuan,

61
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:30,240
find the young lady.

62
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,680
She can confirm his alibi.

63
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:32,840
Yang Dezhi.

64
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:34,560
No.

65
00:02:34,848 --> 00:02:36,016
Don't get her involved.

66
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:41,280
Please.

67
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:51,040
A rich girl

68
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:52,040
who wears Chanel No. 5.

69
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:53,840
I'm sure she comes

70
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:55,720
from a very strict family.

71
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,520
If her father finds out

72
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:58,480
that his daughter spent

73
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:00,360
half the night

74
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,480
with a bunch of grown men.

75
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,360
Young Master Zhao.

76
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:07,920
Shaoshang.

77
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:11,920
I'm begging you.

78
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,720
I'd rather go to jail

79
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:15,080
than drag her into this.

80
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,080
Then off to jail you go.

81
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,320
Stop grabbing me.

82
00:03:17,980 --> 00:03:18,976
Or else, I'll ask her out.

83
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,240
She'll never like a guy like you!

84
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,280
A guy like me?

85
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:23,360
Back to business!

86
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:26,100
Why did you buy cinnabar and lamp oil

87
00:03:26,112 --> 00:03:27,080
at the temple yesterday?

88
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:30,600
Talk.

89
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,600
There's a ring

90
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,560
in my left coat pocket.

91
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:43,880
Yang Dezhi.

92
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:52,720
What?

93
00:03:53,328 --> 00:03:54,160
Planning to propose?

94
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:55,000
Cinnabar.

95
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:55,800
Fake.

96
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,440
Taoists use it for making elixirs.

97
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:59,200
Once it's polished,
it looks like a ruby.

98
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:01,760
It's only temporary.

99
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:04,720
One day, when I
make something of myself,

100
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,360
I'll buy her a real one.

101
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:10,040
The biggest, most beautiful ruby
in all of Beijing.

102
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,800
The biggest, most beautiful ruby
in all of Beijing

103
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:18,880
is in my hand.

104
00:04:20,208 --> 00:04:21,440
If someone wants to buy it,

105
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:22,960
I won't sell it.

106
00:04:38,128 --> 00:04:39,480
You did that on purpose, didn't you?

107
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,480
Did what?

108
00:04:42,864 --> 00:04:43,600
To rile him up.

109
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,580
Make him lose his temper
so I can get even for you.

110
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,600
You really hold grudges.

111
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,840
What do you mean by "on purpose"?

112
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:53,360
Besides,

113
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,040
why don't you say

114
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,920
I took a scolding just to bait him?

115
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,920
I figured you were used to it.

116
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,720
Used to it?

117
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:01,920
Am I that easy to yell at?

118
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,280
If it wasn't Yang Shicheng,

119
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,440
then who was it?

120
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,760
Stop pacing.

121
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:12,200
You're making me dizzy.

122
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,600
I already had Zhao Cai

123
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,240
search all around Beihai.

124
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:17,920
I don't think

125
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,120
the children are in danger.

126
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,360
Why's that?

127
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:26,120
This all comes down to money.

128
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,080
Kidnapping is one thing.

129
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,240
But if anyone gets killed,

130
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,440
it becomes a blood feud

131
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:31,840
that never ends.

132
00:05:31,856 --> 00:05:33,776
Anyone with common sense
would think it through.

133
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,280
Go on.

134
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,840
Eleven kids

135
00:05:40,080 --> 00:05:42,400
all disappeared at six o'clock.

136
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:43,960
Blending into the crowd,

137
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,408
snatching eleven kids at once,

138
00:05:45,410 --> 00:05:47,360
and then taking them
to eleven different locations.

139
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,080
That took planning, discipline,

140
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:50,440
and a lot of people.

141
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:51,440
Other than the army

142
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,440
or the police,

143
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:53,760
who else could do that?

144
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:04,400
I know Beijing City

145
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,680
like the back of my hand.

146
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:10,920
What are you up to again?

147
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:19,000
I want you to beg me.

148
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:28,080
Or you can look on your own.

149
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:29,080
Fine.

150
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:30,080
You got this.

151
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,400
Good luck.

152
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,080
Young Master Zhao,

153
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,000
please help me.

154
00:06:55,584 --> 00:06:56,600
We can't crack this case

155
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,440
without you.

156
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,920
Maybe I haven't cleaned

157
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:02,880
my ears lately.

158
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:04,360
I can't hear you.

159
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,520
Young Master Zhao,

160
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:11,760
could you do me a favor?

161
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,280
We can't solve this case without you.

162
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,440
Oh, please don't say that.

163
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,040
I'm just an ordinary citizen.

164
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:24,000
What do I know about solving cases?

165
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:25,680
Watch your attitude.

166
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:26,880
People are watching.

167
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,160
You're too modest.

168
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,600
Without your help

169
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,320
on the blood fluke case...

170
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,240
Guidance.

171
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,720
Without your guidance,

172
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,400
we'd never have cracked it.

173
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,440
I didn't do much.

174
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,040
I didn't guide anybody.

175
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:00,080
Don't be so humble.

176
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:03,320
Young Master Zhao.

177
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:08,520
You're the real hero behind the scenes.

178
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:09,800
The elite detective.

179
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,360
The Di Renjie of Jingshi.
[*A Tang dynasty statesman]

180
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:13,552
Sherlock Holmes wouldn't be worthy
of shining your shoes.

181
00:08:13,584 --> 00:08:14,600
That's too much.

182
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,040
Don't flatter me into trouble.

183
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:17,800
Can we get back to work now?

184
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:18,680
Yes.

185
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,480
Back to work.

186
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:29,960
My phone's ringing.

187
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:31,160
Why isn't anyone answering?

188
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:33,320
What are you all doing here? Move.

189
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:34,880
Get back to work.

190
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:38,320
Don't eavesdrop on us.

191
00:08:42,780 --> 00:08:44,940
(Yunzhu Pavilion)

192
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:07,140
(Liang Can)

193
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,320
Liang.

194
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,520
How have you been?

195
00:09:19,142 --> 00:09:20,320
Young Master Zhao.

196
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:22,160
Mr. Liang.

197
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,616
A renowned Kun opera enthusiast.

198
00:09:23,616 --> 00:09:25,310
He plays the Dan role.
[*Female role in Chinese opera]

199
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:27,680
You flatter me.

200
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:30,320
You must be

201
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:33,800
the head of Division Four,

202
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:34,760
Yuan Hong.

203
00:09:35,328 --> 00:09:36,400
I've heard a lot about you.

204
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:38,840
You know me?

205
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:42,520
You two recently cracked
a major case together.

206
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:44,200
The whole capital's talking about it.

207
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:47,400
I admire you both.

208
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:49,680
It's a blessing for the people

209
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:52,160
to have police
bring criminals to justice.

210
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:53,480
But...

211
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:54,800
I'm wondering

212
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:57,240
what brings you two

213
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,360
to my humble home today?

214
00:09:58,432 --> 00:09:59,600
We're here to save you.

215
00:10:02,144 --> 00:10:03,520
I heard you paid a hefty price

216
00:10:03,552 --> 00:10:06,760
for a copy of "Jijiupian" last week.
[*Quickly Master [Character] Chapters]

217
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:09,520
It was actually a copy by Yu Helin.

218
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:16,160
You haven't seen it,

219
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:17,200
yet you're so sure.

220
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:19,960
That's why I'm here to take a look.

221
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:24,660
(Jijiupian by Zhao Songxue)

222
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,120
Please.

223
00:10:30,784 --> 00:10:31,952
The first line bears

224
00:10:31,984 --> 00:10:33,920
the red square seal, "Tejianyao."

225
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,600
Below that, the white square seal,
"Shenrong Bichang."

226
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,680
Then the red square seal,
"Linchi Qingshang."

227
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:39,440
And finally,

228
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:42,800
the white square seal, "Qingyinzhai".

229
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,160
Those are all seals

230
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,520
commonly found on Yu's calligraphy.

231
00:10:47,552 --> 00:10:48,848
If you don't believe me,

232
00:10:48,896 --> 00:10:50,440
compare it with his other works.

233
00:10:52,912 --> 00:10:54,400
As expected of Young Master Zhao.

234
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,520
You have my respect.

235
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:00,080
Now that, what can I do for you?

236
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,160
Just name it.

237
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,240
We'd like to ask you something.

238
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:03,840
About what?

239
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,360
Last night's arson case.

240
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:14,320
I'm just a man

241
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:17,040
who enjoys singing opera.

242
00:11:17,152 --> 00:11:18,944
What would I know
about something like that?

243
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:19,760
Mr. Liang,

244
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:21,760
that doesn't sound like you.

245
00:11:21,872 --> 00:11:24,050
In Beijing City,
there's no business, legal or otherwise,

246
00:11:24,064 --> 00:11:25,200
that you don't have a hand in.

247
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:27,320
Who else could pull off
a big scheme like this

248
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:28,920
if not you?

249
00:11:31,696 --> 00:11:33,760
That's a serious accusation,
Young Master Zhao.

250
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,280
What?

251
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:37,160
First, you swindled my man,

252
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,360
and now you're coming after me?

253
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,400
Master Song works for you?

254
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,480
He's just a small fry.

255
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,840
Mr. Liang here

256
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,760
is the real big fish in Beijing.

257
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:52,320
Chief Yuan,

258
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:54,384
I knew nothing

259
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,800
about what Master Song was doing.

260
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,800
But if the police come asking questions,

261
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,160
you'll need evidence.

262
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,160
Master Song isn't important to you.

263
00:12:03,160 --> 00:12:03,920
I know.

264
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:06,720
But your trading houses, your temples,

265
00:12:06,768 --> 00:12:08,200
your escort agencies, and your banks.

266
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:14,840
You must have

267
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:17,400
over a hundred businesses

268
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:19,160
across the city.

269
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:21,200
If you really want us to find evidence,

270
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,800
we can seal them up one by one

271
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:23,920
and search them one by one.

272
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,560
Even if it takes a year or two.

273
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:26,720
How does that sound?

274
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:31,120
Young Master Zhao,

275
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:34,080
even a rabbit will bite

276
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:35,640
when cornered.

277
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:37,320
Oh, come on.

278
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,680
Why would a rabbit chew on weeds

279
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,520
and ignore fresh carrots?

280
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,520
We know you didn't do this.

281
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:44,680
So help us investigate.

282
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:47,640
We wouldn't want to interfere
with your business, would we?

283
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:51,360
Here's the list of the missing children.

284
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:53,160
Why don't you look into it?

285
00:12:57,880 --> 00:12:58,800
You suspect me,

286
00:12:59,184 --> 00:13:01,080
and then expect me
to prove my own innocence?

287
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,880
What kind of police are you?

288
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:05,600
You're bandits.

289
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:08,640
How about this?

290
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:10,880
Master Song

291
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,400
stays in jail.

292
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:13,640
No one lets him out.

293
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,280
Chief Yuan,

294
00:13:21,640 --> 00:13:25,160
you're in uniform.
You can do whatever you please.

295
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:29,280
What about Young Master Zhao?

296
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:31,640
Can you protect him

297
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:33,480
twenty-four hours a day?

298
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:37,680
You're welcome to try.

299
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:57,160
See?

300
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:58,160
I've played

301
00:13:58,480 --> 00:14:00,040
too many female roles.

302
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:01,490
Today I tried playing the Wusheng role,

303
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,790
and I couldn't pull it off.
[*Warrior role in Chinese opera]

304
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:06,720
Why so tense?

305
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:07,560
Alright.

306
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:09,560
Wait for my news.

307
00:14:10,016 --> 00:14:12,240
Mr. Liang, no wonder
you're such a successful businessman.

308
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:12,840
Alright.

309
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,320
We'll be waiting for your message.

310
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,160
They've gone too far.

311
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:26,160
Should we...

312
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,080
One's father sits in the Cabinet,

313
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:36,280
the other's father commands an army.

314
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:38,080
Who are you planning to kill?

315
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:40,240
You'd better know who its master is
when beating a dog.

316
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,840
They're getting far too cocky.

317
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:47,320
If you can take them out, do it cleanly.

318
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:49,600
If you can't,

319
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:51,800
then think about

320
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:54,960
how to make them useful to us.

321
00:15:00,096 --> 00:15:02,160
Why didn't you tell me
you had me arrest Master Song

322
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:04,200
to get to Liang Can?

323
00:15:06,016 --> 00:15:07,056
I've got a lot on my mind.

324
00:15:07,088 --> 00:15:08,976
You expect me
to tell you every little thing?

325
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:10,160
Wouldn't that be annoying?

326
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:14,400
Can Zhao Cai fight?

327
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:16,920
He can't even swat a mosquito.

328
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:18,000
What about shooting?

329
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:18,920
That's easy.

330
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:19,800
I can teach him.

331
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:22,000
What's this about?

332
00:15:22,032 --> 00:15:24,336
You don't really think
Liang Can would dare touch me, do you?

333
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:25,720
He was just talking tough.

334
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:28,280
If he wants to stay
in the antiques business in Beijing,

335
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:29,680
he won't risk making an enemy of me.

336
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:31,880
That confident, huh?

337
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,360
Of course.

338
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,480
Just wait

339
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:36,200
till we crack this case,

340
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:37,480
my picture's in the papers,

341
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:39,320
and I'm famous all over Beijing.

342
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,720
After that, everyone who sees me
will have to bow.

343
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:47,080
Why were you worried back there?

344
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:51,880
As a police officer, it's my duty
to protect the innocent.

345
00:15:55,488 --> 00:15:56,440
If he'd made a move,

346
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:57,520
what would you have done?

347
00:16:00,224 --> 00:16:02,416
Please sit properly
while the vehicle is in motion.

348
00:16:03,184 --> 00:16:04,440
What's with the safety talk?

349
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:06,040
You're putting on a brave face. I know.

350
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:07,920
Safety first.

351
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,600
Safety first?

352
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:10,840
That was the dangerous part.

353
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:13,424
Tell me, with only a few bullets,

354
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,340
what were you going to do
against that many men?

355
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:18,320
Sit properly.

356
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,440
You're a police officer.

357
00:16:21,472 --> 00:16:22,656
You should go after criminals,

358
00:16:22,660 --> 00:16:24,370
not throw your weight around
with me instead.

359
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:27,040
Messing with me, huh, Young Master Zhao?

360
00:16:27,904 --> 00:16:29,580
You let me examine
eleven burned bodies.

361
00:16:29,590 --> 00:16:30,520
They can't be recognized.

362
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:31,280
The workload is bad enough.

363
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:32,160
(Peking Union Medical College)
And you want me to identify

364
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:33,520
(Forensic Report)
them too. Fine.

365
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:34,970
I spent hours bent over these remains.

366
00:16:34,980 --> 00:16:37,030
Turns out they're not human.
How do I identify them?

367
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:37,840
Not human?

368
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:40,000
How can you tell?

369
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:41,440
Humans have long bones.

370
00:16:41,488 --> 00:16:42,760
You know what those are, right?

371
00:16:45,248 --> 00:16:47,500
In biology, there's something called
the Haversian System.

372
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:49,390
We examine cross-sections
of the long bones

373
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,200
(Human Skeleton, Animal Skeleton)
to tell human bones from animal bones.

374
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,600
I've checked every long bone

375
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:53,536
from all eleven remains.

376
00:16:53,540 --> 00:16:54,360
Their Haversian canals

377
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:56,240
are completely different
from those of humans.

378
00:16:56,272 --> 00:16:57,480
So they're not human.

379
00:16:58,160 --> 00:16:58,960
If they're not human,

380
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:01,240
then those kidnapped children

381
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,320
might still be alive.

382
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:05,560
Bad news!

383
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:08,400
Liang Can put everything in the papers.

384
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:10,520
(Rishaw Pullers
Secretly Build Fire Wheels)

385
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:11,560
(Posed as Nezha on the Ghost Festival)
Darned Liang Can.

386
00:17:11,570 --> 00:17:13,400
He said he'd tell us first
if he found anything.

387
00:17:13,410 --> 00:17:14,816
He just went straight to the press.

388
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:16,720
He found out it was a rickshaw puller,

389
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:18,352
but didn't tell us which rickshaw depot.

390
00:17:18,360 --> 00:17:19,560
Scoundrel.

391
00:17:19,560 --> 00:17:21,440
We need to narrow it down fast.

392
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:22,880
If the kidnappers see the newspaper,

393
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:25,120
they might panic
and kill the hostages.

394
00:17:25,840 --> 00:17:26,840
Last night at six,

395
00:17:26,840 --> 00:17:28,880
(Beihai Park)
my son disappeared near Beihai Park.

396
00:17:28,890 --> 00:17:31,480
My granddaughter went missing
at Dongsi Pailou.

397
00:17:31,504 --> 00:17:33,890
(Yilan Hall's Entrance)
My son disappeared outside Yilan Hall.

398
00:17:34,832 --> 00:17:35,952
Songpo Library.

399
00:17:35,984 --> 00:17:36,600
(Songpo Library)

400
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:37,790
(Xinghua Alley)
Xinghua Alley.

401
00:17:37,808 --> 00:17:38,640
Wenjin Street.

402
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,660
(Wenjin Street)

403
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:44,800
My rickshaw was stolen.
Six o'clock at Dongsi South Street.

404
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:46,336
Not just the rickshaw, my monkey too.

405
00:17:46,380 --> 00:17:47,740
(Six)

406
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,440
There's a rickshaw depot

407
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:51,240
by Dongsi Pailou.

408
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:53,360
Children,

409
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,320
time to eat.

410
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:00,400
Here you go.

411
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:02,880
Eat slowly.

412
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:05,960
Mister, when can we go home?

413
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:07,720
No rush.

414
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:10,080
Your parents are busy.

415
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,400
Wait for a couple more days.

416
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:13,800
I don't want steamed buns.
They're awful.

417
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,000
I want egg fried rice.

418
00:18:15,080 --> 00:18:16,280
I want chocolate.

419
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:17,720
I want Coca-Cola.

420
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:21,880
- Me too!
- Me too!

421
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,840
Enough.

422
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:24,680
Enough.

423
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:27,160
I've got some candy.

424
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:29,640
Have a piece first.

425
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:31,920
- I want one!
- I want one!

426
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:33,000
Alright. Easy.

427
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:34,640
There's enough for everyone.

428
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:35,480
Slow down.

429
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:37,680
- Me too!
- Me too!

430
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:39,760
It's good.

431
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,200
So good.

432
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:45,840
I want that one.

433
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:46,440
Yummy.

434
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:49,860
(Six)

435
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:50,960
Ai!

436
00:18:51,040 --> 00:18:51,960
Nobody move!

437
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:52,800
Ai!

438
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:53,840
Ai!

439
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:54,880
Ai!

440
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:56,520
What's wrong?

441
00:18:58,520 --> 00:19:00,360
Grandson, wake up!

442
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:02,160
What is this?

443
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:03,760
You!

444
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:05,080
What did you feed the kids?

445
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:06,080
Steamed buns.

446
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:06,920
Candy.

447
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:08,240
No.

448
00:19:08,912 --> 00:19:09,960
Get them to the hospital.

449
00:19:09,960 --> 00:19:13,400
(End of Episode 7)

450
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,520
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

451
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:17,060
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

452
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:18,310
♪However, the world changes♪

453
00:19:18,310 --> 00:19:20,230
♪You'll still be by my side♪

454
00:19:20,230 --> 00:19:21,920
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

455
00:19:21,920 --> 00:19:23,490
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

456
00:19:23,490 --> 00:19:25,060
♪If this is my final chapter♪

457
00:19:25,060 --> 00:19:27,560
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
